<subSubSection id="7592641C9FB8BFA9A950D064B8FE9D1F" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="notes">
<paragraph id="03E456159BFBD38D02D99EE9CB3B1F7E" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14531628522CAFD83F3D6F3A2B453C12" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicName id="104769CF5A859EE7F0D06EEA60FE5C5C" genus="H." lsidName="H. rubiginosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" rank="species" species="rubiginosum">
<emphasis id="E725018B43EC1AB88918B11DB29C31AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">H. rubiginosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="ABE5BF6F2C687801ADC10DFC87AB1F0B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">sensu stricto</emphasis>
is a very common fungus in the temperate Northern hemisphere (
<bibRefCitation id="74337D6F1628A077F9BE8D809E4DC41B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2509/naf2008.003.0075" author="Stadler, M" journalOrPublisher="North American Fungi" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 73" refId="B36" refString="Stadler, M, Fournier, J, Granmo, A, Beltran-Tejera, E, 2008. The &quot;red Hypoxylons&quot; of the temperate and subtropical Northern Hemisphere. North American Fungi 3: 1 - 73, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2509/naf2008.003.0075" title="The &quot; red Hypoxylons &quot; of the temperate and subtropical Northern Hemisphere." url="https://doi.org/10.2509/naf2008.003.0075" volume="3" year="2008">Stadler et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
) and may occur in subtropical areas, such as Florida, USA (
<bibRefCitation id="858114F12A9A0F605A4EDCB16678714C" author="Ju, YM" journalOrPublisher="APS Press, St. Paul" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" refId="B16" refString="Ju, YM, Rogers, JD, 1996. A revision of the genus Hypoxylon. Mycologia Memoir n° 20. APS Press, St. Paul" title="A revision of the genus Hypoxylon. Mycologia Memoir n ° 20." year="1996">Ju and Rogers 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Most of the characters of the Iranian specimens are in accordance with previous descriptions (
<bibRefCitation id="07DD36A8FBDBBF35265FE3327BFFF115" author="Stadler, M" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" pagination="187 - 211" refId="B33" refString="Stadler, M, Wollweber, H, Fournier, J, 2004. A host-specific species of Hypoxylon from France, and notes on the chemotaxonomy of the &quot; Hypoxylon rubiginosum complex&quot;. Mycotaxon 90: 187 - 211" title="A host-specific species of Hypoxylon from France, and notes on the chemotaxonomy of the &quot; Hypoxylon rubiginosum complex &quot;." volume="90" year="2004">Stadler et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
), aside from insignificant variations in the size of ascospores.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B77A57C1951C6F9576A3002AB6DBCD18" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.65.50946.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/403604" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
